        "id": 1001907
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-09-11T23:26:34Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I believe that as of Go 1.14 defers are much lower overhead, and the compiler is better with inlining; I would be surprised if the defer bit here was a source of problems.\n\nThe PANIC bit, on the other hand, is probably not very performant... but we also ~never have errors here.\n\nIf I can replace the interfaces with a *bytes.Buffer, I can assume some things about the implementation here (and maybe just remove the returned errors from most of these).",
